<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-28T09:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-28T09:44:00-05:00" n="455" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d455">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.00/1157: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-28T14:00:00-00:44">April 28,
                                    1942—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2:59 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>136. Secretary of State Simpson states that President Barclay is anxious
                            to adjourn Liberian Legislature which has been in continuous session
                            since last October, longest in history, in view of his understanding
                            that defense forces would be in Liberia by end of April, he would like
                            to know when conditions will permit him to submit agreement to
                            Legislature for approval.</p>
                        <p>Legislature, to my knowledge, is being held for express purpose of
                            submission of agreement which to avoid publicity, it was agreed to
                            withhold until adequate defense forces reached Liberia.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>